{"word":"H7014 - קַיִן - Qayin - kah'-yin - Cain","slug":"H7014","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">קַיִן</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Qayin"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kah'-yin"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cain"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E7;&#x05D9;&#x05DF; - qayin</b> - <i>kah'-yin</i><p/>The same as <a href=\"#/H7013\">H7013</a> (with a play upon the affinity to <a href=\"#/H7069\">H7069</a>); <i>Kajin</i>, the name of the first child, also of a place in Palestine, and of an Oriental tribe: - Cain, Kenite (-s)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6969\">H6969</a>, <a href=\"#/H7013\">H7013</a>, <a href=\"#/H7015\">H7015</a>, <a href=\"#/H7016\">H7016</a>, <a href=\"#/H7017\">H7017</a>, <a href=\"#/H7018\">H7018</a>"}]}